SGT POWELL broke outward while being hustled for the lead, got forward position into the first turn but was three wide, continued to race three to four wide down the backstretch and into the far turn, came under pressure with about three furlongs to run, made a tepid bid five wide into the stretch but faltered. HOT JOURNEY broke outward at the start, was far behind to the far turn, made up a little bit of ground in the stretch then had to alter course when MACHO CHROME stopped in his path. MACHO CHROME broke well and was sent to get a share of the early lead, was a little hard to handle going into the first turn and put AZURE STAR (IRE) in tight quarters briefly, those two raced together down the backstretch and into the far turn, took a brief lead at the head of the stretch, became erratic and lost action nearing the furlong marker, dropped to the rear in the final sixteenth and was not persevered with to the finish.
